{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4030f732-eef8-4962-8549-0556687e5240","content":"Two things change with MTP:\n\n1. **Syntax** — VSTest's `--filter` uses `Property~Value & Property=Value`. MTP uses `--treenode-filter` with glob paths and `[Trait=Value]` brackets.\n\n2. **Passing it** — MTP args go after `--` on the `dotnet test` command line.\n\n**Translation:**\n\n```\n# Old (VSTest / xUnit v2)\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n\n# New (MTP / xUnit v3)\ndotnet test -- --treenode-filter \"/**/*IntegrationTests*/**[Category=Smoke]\"\n```\n\n**How it maps:**\n\n| VSTest filter part | MTP treenode-filter equivalent |\n|---|---|\n| `FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests` | `/**/*IntegrationTests*/**` (glob match on the test tree path) |\n| `Category=Smoke` | `[Category=Smoke]` (trait/property filter in brackets) |\n| `&` (AND) | Combined inline — the glob selects nodes, the bracket filters traits on those nodes |\n\nThe tree path structure is `/Assembly/Namespace.Class/Method`, so `/**/*IntegrationTests*/**` matches any test under a class containing \"IntegrationTests\".","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f297e3f8-e79b-406a-b416-8f2e37374ca7","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is migrating from xUnit v2 to xUnit v3 with Microsoft Testing Platform (MTP). The key changes for filtering:\n\n1. With xUnit v2 + VSTest, `--filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"` uses VSTest filter syntax where `~` means \"contains\" and `&` is AND.\n\n2. With xUnit v3 + MTP (`UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner=true`), the filtering mechanism changes. MTP uses `--filter` but with a different syntax. The test executable itself handles filtering.\n\nKey differences:\n\n\n- MTP uses `--treenode-filter` instead of `--filter` for the filtering mechanism\n- The filter syntax shifts from VSTest's property-based approach to MTP's path-based syntax, like `/**/*IntegrationTests*` for name matching\n- Traits are handled differently in the new system\n\n, requiring adjusted property syntax\n\nSo the distinction is clear: VSTest filters use `FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke` with operators like `~` for contains and `&` for AND, where `Category` corresponds to xUnit's `Trait` attributes. With MTP enabled, the filter gets passed as `--treenode-filter` using a completely different format based on tree node paths rather than property matching. Completing the filter syntax and clarifying how MTP handles test filtering—when using the Microsoft Testing Platform runner, `dotnet test --filter` still works but I need to use the `--treenode-filter` approach with the proper tree path structure like `/Assembly/Namespace.Class/MethodName` and wildcards to match segments.","outputTokens":1366,"requestId":"7031:39211A:DB71EC1:F1B31B7:69F2A91B"},"id":"c6d26945-c373-402c-acaa-1e21feb9be24","timestamp":"2026-04-30T00:58:31.821Z","parentId":"0c120a3c-e687-4718-a066-1cb1c1925195"}
